      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can see why you'd think that, but trust me, it's not that simple. Your body's got a complex system going on, and just stopping one medication and starting another isn't going to magically clear out the old stuff. Plus, St. John's Wort can actually increase the levels of serotonin in your system, which could lead to some pretty intense side effects, especially if you're trying to taper off Zoloft. I'd recommend you try a different approach, like gradually tapering off Zoloft under the guidance of a professional.",
      "source": "target",
